      "content": "I strongly advise against attempting to use ear drops or self-medicating without professional guidance. Your symptoms, especially the sudden and complete loss of hearing, could indicate more serious issues beneath the surface. Ear drops may actually push the wax or debris further into your ear, potentially exacerbating the problem. It's crucial to let a medical professional, such as an ear, nose, and throat (ENT) specialist or a primary care physician, assess your condition. They can provide a proper diagnosis and recommend the best course of treatment.",
